messages.content: Meriad came here and put Vega in her bed, tucking her in before going back to the kitchen
Some time later, Aion enters, trying to keep quiet.
Vega snnzzz
She wasn’t immediately sleepy, she pulled out a notebook and began writing down a few ideas for her big party.
Shes purring in her sleep
Aion noticed this, ears peeking up.
Vegas awake now
@Gekitoutsu Rispba
“O-Oh, hi, Vega...”
She yawned "Hi Aion!!!" She smiled
“I-I had an idea, you...Wanna hear it?”
She nodded
“Wh-What if we did a p-pool party?”
"I....cant swim......But I thimk if mama helps me I will be ok!!"
“O-Oh...” she nodded.
Shes excited
She started to smile, wagging her tail.
"We should tell the others!!!"
“ I think I’ve talked to Meriad about it... at least mentioned it....”
"Lets go tell Iuvenis then!!!!" She smiled
She blushed faintly. “O-OK...”
Vega was completely oblivious as she took Aions hand
She looked cautious, but then it turned into a smile.
Off she lead her to the kitchen! She was gonna be a brave girl this time
Vegas running  around. She Does Not Wanna Get Ready
Opal knocked on the door and opened it "Hello hello"

Opal picked her up "You know, the biiiig event is very soon ! You should get ready !"
"I don't wanna!!!!" She stuck her tounge out "I wanna run around!"
"Don't worry, you'll have all.the time to run around once you'll be ready"
"....Ok!!!! Can you help me Mama?????" She asked
She nodded "Of course sweetheart !"
She cheered "Yay!!!!"

She kicked  her little  kegs as her hair was brushed

Vegas excited

She giggled  and went over to Aion "Aion!!!!!! Play princess with me!!!"
@Gekitoutsu Rispba
Aion nodded, tail wagging a bit. “Uh... sure?”
"Im excited  to be a flower girl!!!" She giggled
Opal chuckled and left the room, heading to #vulpes-room
“Y-Yeah! Me too!”
"Do you wanna go see if Iuvenis is ready and can play????"
She nodded.
Dhe took her hand and went to Iuvenis' room
The world glitches in the room as a math covered stand suddenly appears. It seems to be in excruciating pain, panting heavily before collapsing on the floor.
Aion squeaked, curling up on her bed, before realizing what had just appeared. “A-Aleph-0?!”
It was unconscious, still laying on the floor and glitching.
She cautiously tapped it with her tail.
It was still 'breathing', just very very tired.
She sighed in relief.
After quite a few minutes of just...laying there, it started to gain consciousness slowly
“A-Are you all right, Aleph?”
"Where a-a-am I? W-w-who are y-y-you?"
“It’s me, Joss!” She said, hand on her chest.
"Y-y-you don't look like J-J-Joss! I-I-I don't know w-what happened!" It starts to panic.
“H-Hey, hey, calm down! You’re in the void, where the multiverse is made!”
"W-w-where's E-earth? D-did I g-g-glitch t-t-too hard?"
“Earth? We’re not on any earth!”
"I-I must have g-g-glitched too h-hard!" It tries to stand up, but fails.
“P-Please, take it easy!”
"...W-why do y-you look different?"
“This is my true self. I’m the most pure form of joss in any and All realities.”
"So, you're an infinite form of joss? The end result of all josses?"
“I...guess you could say that.”
"I-Is it just us here in the void?"
“N-No, far from it!”
"Can you show me around?" It tries again to stand up, and fails again.
“N-Not much of it, there’s a... revolution happening...but I can show you what I can.” She said. “I think I can carry you-wait, no...”
"Yeah, I don't want to hurt my only f-f-friend."
“I-I’m your...only friend?”
"So far. I w-w-wish I had more."
“Well... Most of the Muns here are nice, I think they’ll like you...”
( @Bunnie )
"I hope so..."
She smiled a bit at them.
It smiles a bit back.
“S-Stay close, all right? Don’t want you getting hurt...”
"Y-y-yeah, I don't w-w-want to get hurt more than I already am."
Aion nodded, getting off of her bed.
Aleph tries to stand, this time with more success.
"There we go! Let's g-g-get walking."
“O-OK!” She led it out.
It followed behind Aion
@Pastel warrior of hope!!!

Meriad set Arándano down on the bed "Hm....She definitely seems to have a broken wing....and she probably hit her head when she fell....." She grabbed a washcloth and got it wet using her ability to control water. She gently cleaned up the others head with it before leaving it on her head to helo try and ease her headache. "Hm.....Ive never fixed a broken wing before...."

“But-“
“Can you?”
Some of the Aion’s were also in the room, with a few more at the door- including some who picked up her necklace.
"It not safe for me to try.....I could damage it more..." She sighed
She sighed.

Buneries is here "Oh geez....Her wing really does look bad...." She quickly got to work fixing it up. "She wont be able to fly for a while so its safer for her to stay here if Dominus is ok with it...She also has a small concussion. She needs lots of bedrest."
A small groan came from Arándano as she began to wake up. "Ugh...."
“I might be able to help. I have some scents that can aid her concussions.” Aemilius said.
Buneries nodded "Perfect. Thank you." She smiled
She pulled out a vial and poured it around Arandano’s head.
Arándano was very confused because shes never seen these people before. Shes never really met the plasma before.
“There. That should help make your head feel better.”
"Thank you...." She smiled a small bit. "Sucks I broke my wing...."

“Don’t worry. Bunieres is a medic that is beyond your species. You’ll be fine soon.”
“Y-You can stay here for a while!”
“I’m sure Vega would be fine with it.”

"With my abilities your wing should be healed in no time!!" Buneries grinned

"Alright..."
“You’re safe with us!” Another clone said, bringing in the necklace.
"Oh! My necklace...." She gently takes it.

“It broke when you fell on the roof.”
“I don’t know if I can fix it though...” 
“Can’t help you there, kid.” Aemilius said.
"Its fine...Im the one who made it...." She opens the locket. Inside is a picture of her as Darla and the basement boys. "I care more about the locket....."

“Th-Thats...” Aion stared at it, her ears lowering. “That’s them...” 
“How’d you get a picture from the lower worlds up to here?” Aemilus asked, surprised.
"Im not sure...but....I cherish it alot....They are my friends these boys...." She hummed "I always end up falling in love with Lügner...." Arándano chuckled a bit

“One of them is my friend too!”
“My best friend!”
“I hope we have a story like yours sometime...”
"Oh? Who? Point him out!" She hummed
One of them pointed at hoshi. “Him! Iuvenis!”
"He....has a mun...?" She was suprised "Well...I did meet the muns of Lügner and Jisatsu....Wait- Does that mean Soba has a mun too?! I-I wonder.....if Rigel has one..."

She nodded. “He’s here, actually! He’s one of the guards!” 
“I don’t know about a rigel, though...”
Her tail starts to wag and she tries to get out of bed. She wants to see her friends again....
“Don’t. You still need to rest.” Aemilus said.

Shes stubborn but realizes this when she nearly collapsed again. Luckily Buneries caught her. 

Meriad had gone off to see if she could find Iuvenis or Veteris. Perhaps one of them would like to see Arándano

“Should’ve listened.” She sighed, shaking her head. 
“H-How come we’ve never met in the lesser void...?”
“...You’ve been in the lesser void?”
"Well...whos your human...?" She asked, now back in the bed

“I-I already said, it’s Joss Kujo.”
“I-I dont look that different, I don’t think...”
“Unbelievable...” Aemilius said. “No wonder the revolution happened in your lifetime.”
"I....think ive seen you before...." She smiled
“M-Maybe? Once or twice?”
She nodded
“That’s beside the point!” Aemilius said. “Why did you two muck around in the lesser void?”
"Because why not? It was fun....I met new people..."

Aion nodded, meekly looking up at Aemilius.  
She scoffed a bit. “I don’t understand the appeal of the lesser void. It’s so... chaotic. Nothing makes sense there, and realities so easily interact. 
“I-I know, but without it I don’t think I would have made as many friends as I have...”
Arándano nodded in agreement
Aemilius gave a small nod. “Hmm.”
Arándano has been here for a little whike now and is feeling better. She still cant fly but shes able to stand up and walk around without getting a massive headache.
